 Data grandmasters, Globacom, has unveiled a special Valentine promotion designed to ensure that its subscribers have a memorable and delightful love season. According to the details of the exciting offer released by the company on Monday, subscribers will receive up to 36GB of free data which they can share with their loved ones when they purchase two smartphones from Globacom’s retail outlets called Glo World located in several cities across the country. The Valentine promo began on Monday, February 8, and will end on Monday, February 22, 2021, while the data slabs on offer will be determined by the price of the particular smartphones  purchased by the subscriber, the telecom operator explained.  The offer  ranges from 3GB to 36GB of free data which will be availed the subscriber over the next six months. Several of the leading phone brands are available in the promotion, including iPhone, Samsung, Nokia, Infinix, Tecno, Vivo, Imose and Itel. Apart from the generous data offer, Globacom added, “The subscriber is rest assured of the genuineness of the phones which come with warranties and after sales support from the manufacturers. The prices at the Gloworld outlets are also the most competitive in the market”. “This offer is our way of adding flavour to our customers’ Valentine Season enjoyment.  We expect that our customers will be engaged in a lot of online activities before and around February 14, so we decided to make it easier for them to buy genuine devices at affordable prices for themselves and their loved ones”, the company noted. “They will also use the free data bundles accruing from the promo to reach their loved ones to express their feelings of love and commitment,” Globacom said, urging subscribers to make use of the opportunity to show their loved ones how much they care.